  <skos:Concept rdf:about="http://localhost:8000/ec16a2bd-df80-48fc-b961-ecdf506540bc">
    <dcterms:identifier>http://localhost:8000/ec16a2bd-df80-48fc-b961-ecdf506540bc</dcterms:identifier>
    <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">Condition Protective Fencing</skos:prefLabel>
    <skos:inScheme rdf:resource="http://localhost:8000/cf2a6919-f8e7-4d06-a5e0-07056aa701f9"/>
    <arches:sortorder rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">6</arches:sortorder>
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">Reason	

The planning authority wishes to protect archaeological remains during development works.  

Condition	

No development shall commence until details of  fencing, signage and other control measures to protect archaeological remains in-situ have been submitted by the applicant and approved by the planning authority.  The approved programme must be implemented in accordance with the approved details and maintained for the duration of operational works.
</skos:scopeNote>
